00:11:56.290 --> 00:11:59.720
In app protocol, they are the unit of information.

00:11:59.730 --> 00:12:03.370
So essentially, everything you do in the app protocol, if

00:12:03.380 --> 00:12:04.910
you like something, it's a record, it's a

00:12:04.920 --> 00:12:07.400
lexicon that gets emitted and stored on a personal data

00:12:07.550 --> 00:12:07.880
server.

00:12:07.890 --> 00:12:11.200
And that's sort of, like, the information that's

00:12:11.200 --> 00:12:12.810
traveling around, that's a lexicon.

00:12:12.870 --> 00:12:15.620
Apps don't need to declare their own types.

00:12:15.630 --> 00:12:16.800
They can grab existing ones.

00:12:16.810 --> 00:12:19.190
It's cool that I've seen a lot of developers kind

00:12:19.230 --> 00:12:21.610
