.

00:18:05.610 --> 00:18:10.640
Oscar Morgenstein and John von Neumann made the book

00:18:10.640 --> 00:18:13.580
The Theory of Games and Economic Behavior, which is about...

00:18:13.590 --> 00:18:16.670
which kind of brought game theory as a mathematical field into what

00:18:16.680 --> 00:18:18.680
was the social science before of economics.

00:18:18.690 --> 00:18:23.220
And that kind of started this movement of economics that eventually led

00:18:23.220 --> 00:18:26.750
to the market's creation and sort of, like, the

00:18:26.930 --> 00:18:29.580
, you know, zero-sum games was exactly what

00:18:29.580 --> 00:18:33.050
they built and how, you know, if I get money

00:18:33.210 --> 00:18:34.780
, it's at the expense of someone else.

00:18:34.790 --> 00:18:38.160
Since that time, economic theory has moved to positive sum.

00:18:38.170 --> 00:18:39.440
There's, like, all kinds of, like, goofy

00:18:39.440 --> 00:18:41.780
things they're doing, and this is where my economics minor

00:18:41.780 --> 00:18:42.260
stops.

00:18:42.270 --> 00:18:46.060
